pt.2
how the republican party quietly does the bidding of white supremacists

by russ feingold
if republican lawmakers want to distinguish themselves from trump’s comments, they need to do more than type out 144 characters on their phone. they need to take a hard look at their party’s agenda.
a good start would be with voting rights. let’s see lawmakers like john kasich in ohio immediately stop the state’s intended purging of voting records. let’s see wisconsin lawmakers throw out their gerrymandered district map and form a non-partisan redistricting commission.
let’s see strict voter id laws criticized with the same vitriol that republicans used in responding to the events in charlottesville. let’s see republicans call out their own agenda, and openly recognize the connection between the agenda of the racist alt-right and that of the republican party.
anything short of radical change to the republican party’s war on voters of color is merely feigned outrage. even if the white supremacists are condemned, even if the entire republican party rises up in self-professed outrage at white supremacists, if voter suppression and other such racist policies survive, the white supremacists are winning. and america is losing.

russ feingold is a former senator for wisconsin

text: every day we vote for women. we provide informed consent free of coercion and manipulation. we don't withhold information. we provide trauma-informed care. we offer and ask. we do things with women not to them. we understand that women exist in a system that wasn't built by them or for them, and as midwives and women, we exist in that system too. while i appreciate the conversations about "improving birth," the truth is that lydia and i aren't just talking about it, we're quite literally on the front lines of protecting women's rights every single day. it is not an easy job, and there are many days that in making it better for the women we serve, we make it harder for ourselves. let's not sit around discussing how we can make the world better, go vote for someone who will. #pleasevote #govote #fikamidwifery

a good start would be with voting rights. let’s see lawmakers like john kasich in ohio immediately stop the state’s intended purging of voting records. let’s see wisconsin lawmakers throw out their gerrymandered district map and form a non-partisan redistricting commission.

russ feingold is a former senator for wisconsin

text:
having been a teacher for many years, i had always wanted to organize a program that solely focused on empowering girls and preparing them for the world. i wanted to share inspirational stories about successful women and women who had changed the world. i wanted to provide a space for them to reflect, question, and have very real and open conversations about societal pressures and gender issues.  i wanted to give them the tools to help them successfully meet future challenges with strength and support. 
now as a mother to a 1-year-old girl, i realize more than ever the void that exists between women and the dire need to come together more to take action and change the world. today i hope to open up a space where all women young and old from whatever walks of life can feel inspired and share in the analyzing, understanding and defining what truly is our raw inner voice. #women #yeswecan #feminism #womanempowerment #inspiringwomen #motherhood #womensrights #metoo #metoomovement

text:
_ vote _
i was one of those people who never saw the point in voting because i thought it wouldn't make a difference. i also hadn't realized the importance of midterms until this year. i despise politics because i feel there's no heart in it. and, at this point, it becomes a means to keep control over the people it was made to protect. then it hit me like a ton of bricks that following along with the notion that it wouldn't make a difference was probably exactly what those people in power wanted me to believe, and that i was making it easier for them. we do have voices, and this is definitely one of the times to use them. at the very least, we'll make it harder for the wrong people to stay in control, until the day comes that they just can't bullshit us anymore... go out and vote. you voting is a big "fuck you" to those who think you don't matter. let them know we're here and that we have a say in our future and the world we want to create for our families... ✌🏽✊🏽 #vote #ivoted #votewithus #aloneiamone #togetherwearemany #midtermelections2018 #stickittotheman #imatter #wematter #wehaveasay #somosmas #blacklivesmatter #translivesmatter #lgbtq #metoo #therevolutionisfemale #ageofthewomb
